--====== Mouse Sensitivity Settings =========--


--##############################################################################--
--##############           Ready Sensitivity Setting           #################--
--##############################################################################--
--##############  For Sensitivity 0.5 Set the CSMacro to 4     #################--
--##############  For Sensitivity 1.0 Set the CSMacro to 2     #################--
--##############  For Sensitivity 1.5 Set the CSMacro to 1.33  #################--
--##############  For Sensitivity 2.0 Set the CSMacro to 1     #################--
--##############  For Sensitivity 2.5 Set the CSMacro to 0.75  #################--
--##############  For Sensitivity 3.0 Set the CSMacro to 0.65  #################--
--##############  For Sensitivity 4.0 Set the CSMacro to 0.50  #################--
--##############################################################################--
--##############################################################################--

local CSMacro = 1  --> !! Change it for your own Sensitivity Setting! Check List above! 

--[[
It's as default for Sensitivity 2 - Check the list above for your own Sensitivity Setting.
However you can play around to fit it for your own sensitivity setting.
If you're using a different resolution etc. with this setting you may can fit it 

If your aim goes too much up make the setting higher if it's goes too much down make the CSMacro setting a bit lower.
For example if you're using Sensitivity 2.2 make the number 0.85 or any number around that which feels comfortable for you.
Installation instruction for Logitech: https://csmacro.com/how-to-install-logitech-g-hub/  
]]--



--====== MOUSE BUTTON SETTING (RMB)+(LMB) or only (LMB) =========--


-- If you want to use left click (LMB) for using the macro change it from local click = 3 to 1
-- As default you have to hold right (RMB) & left click (LMB) for using the macro.
-- with chaning it to local click = 1 you need to hold only left mouse button (LMB). 
-- For (LMB) only 1
-- For (RMB)+(LMB) 3


local click = 3



--[[ 	*NEW* SUPERGLIDE FEATURE *BETA*

What is SuperGlide ?
A superglide is a movement tech that allows you to gain high speed after mantling an object. 
Instead of moving at slow or normal speeds, you get sent flying forward (or to the side if you use a side input).
If you don't know what it is for more information search in google/youtube Apex Legends SuperGlide

For using the SuperGlide you have to assign a button to it, same as a weapon assignment to your Mouse/Keyboard ]]--

local SuperGlide = nil

-- Below is the Timer setting for the SuperGlide. 
